[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6494,
        "end_time": 9888,
        "text": "An enduring myth says we use\nonly 10% of our brain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9912,
        "end_time": 13477,
        "text": "the other 90% standing idly by\nfor spare capacity."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 13920,
        "end_time": 16400,
        "text": "Hucksters promised to unlock\nthat hidden potential"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 16424,
        "end_time": 19483,
        "text": "with methods &quot;based on neuroscience,&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 19507,
        "end_time": 21706,
        "text": "but all they really unlock is your wallet."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 22225,
        "end_time": 25285,
        "text": "Two-thirds of the public\nand nearly half of science teachers"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 25309,
        "end_time": 27836,
        "text": "mistakenly believe the 10% myth."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 27860,
        "end_time": 30035,
        "text": "In the 1890s, William James,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 30059,
        "end_time": 32815,
        "text": "the father of American psychology, said,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 32839,
        "end_time": 35233,
        "text": "&quot;Most of us do not meet\nour mental potential.&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 35692,
        "end_time": 37337,
        "text": "James meant this as a challenge,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 37361,
        "end_time": 39802,
        "text": "not an indictment of scant brain usage."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 39826,
        "end_time": 41711,
        "text": "But the misunderstanding stuck."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 42016,
        "end_time": 45223,
        "text": "Also, scientists couldn&#39;t\nfigure out for a long time"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 45247,
        "end_time": 47553,
        "text": "the purpose of our massive frontal lobes"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 47577,
        "end_time": 50139,
        "text": "or broad areas of the parietal lobe."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 50163,
        "end_time": 53057,
        "text": "Damage didn&#39;t cause motor\nor sensory deficits,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 53081,
        "end_time": 56020,
        "text": "so authorities concluded\nthey didn&#39;t do anything."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 56687,
        "end_time": 59442,
        "text": "For decades, these parts\nwere called silent areas,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 59466,
        "end_time": 61101,
        "text": "their function elusive."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 61125,
        "end_time": 63230,
        "text": "We&#39;ve since learned that they underscore"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 63254,
        "end_time": 64944,
        "text": "executive and integrative ability,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 64968,
        "end_time": 67199,
        "text": "without which, we would hardly be human."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 67223,
        "end_time": 69239,
        "text": "They are crucial to abstract reasoning,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 69263,
        "end_time": 70784,
        "text": "planning, weighing decisions"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 70808,
        "end_time": 73213,
        "text": "and flexibly adapting to circumstances."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 73779,
        "end_time": 77310,
        "text": "The idea that 9\/10 of your brain\nsits idly by in your skull"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 77334,
        "end_time": 80564,
        "text": "looks silly when we calculate\nhow the brain uses energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 81064,
        "end_time": 82825,
        "text": "Rodent and canine brains"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 82849,
        "end_time": 85424,
        "text": "consume 5% of total body energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 85448,
        "end_time": 87261,
        "text": "Monkey brains use 10%."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 87717,
        "end_time": 89096,
        "text": "An adult human brain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 89120,
        "end_time": 91808,
        "text": "which accounts for only 2%\nof the body&#39;s mass,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 91832,
        "end_time": 95446,
        "text": "consumes 20% of daily glucose burned."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 95884,
        "end_time": 98226,
        "text": "In children, that figure is 50%,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 98250,
        "end_time": 100386,
        "text": "and in infants, 60%."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 100964,
        "end_time": 104194,
        "text": "This is far more than expected\nfor their relative brain sizes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 104218,
        "end_time": 106612,
        "text": "which scale in proportion to body size."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 106636,
        "end_time": 108893,
        "text": "Human ones weigh 1.5 kilograms,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 108917,
        "end_time": 110616,
        "text": "elephant brains 5 kg,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 110640,
        "end_time": 112726,
        "text": "and whale brains 9 kg,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 112750,
        "end_time": 114643,
        "text": "yet on a per weight basis,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 114667,
        "end_time": 118373,
        "text": "humans pack in more neurons\nthan any other species."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 118397,
        "end_time": 121019,
        "text": "This dense packing\nis what makes us so smart."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 121585,
        "end_time": 123544,
        "text": "There is a trade-off between body size"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 123568,
        "end_time": 125590,
        "text": "and the number of neurons a primate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 125614,
        "end_time": 127165,
        "text": "including us, can sustain."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 127189,
        "end_time": 130666,
        "text": "A 25 kg ape has to eat 8 hours a day"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 130690,
        "end_time": 133751,
        "text": "to uphold a brain with 53 billion neurons."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 134673,
        "end_time": 135993,
        "text": "The invention of cooking,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 136017,
        "end_time": 137494,
        "text": "one and half million years ago,"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 137518,
        "end_time": 139319,
        "text": "gave us a huge advantage."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 139343,
        "end_time": 142336,
        "text": "Cooked food is rendered\nsoft and predigested"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 142360,
        "end_time": 143618,
        "text": "outside of the body."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 143642,
        "end_time": 146074,
        "text": "Our guts more easily absorb its energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 146466,
        "end_time": 149153,
        "text": "Cooking frees up time\nand provides more energy"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 149177,
        "end_time": 150979,
        "text": "than if we ate food stuffs raw"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 151003,
        "end_time": 153013,
        "text": "and so we can sustain brains"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 153037,
        "end_time": 156038,
        "text": "with 86 billion densely packed neurons."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 156474,
        "end_time": 158030,
        "text": "40% more than the ape."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 158548,
        "end_time": 159834,
        "text": "Here&#39;s how it works."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 159858,
        "end_time": 161709,
        "text": "Half the calories a brain burns"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 161733,
        "end_time": 163924,
        "text": "go towards simply keeping\nthe structure intact"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 163948,
        "end_time": 166678,
        "text": "by pumping sodium and potassium ions"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 166702,
        "end_time": 169891,
        "text": "across membranes\nto maintain an electrical charge."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 170336,
        "end_time": 173178,
        "text": "To do this, the brain\nhas to be an energy hog."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 173202,
        "end_time": 174888,
        "text": "It consumes an astounding"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 174912,
        "end_time": 180357,
        "text": "3.4 x 10^21 ATP molecules per minute,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 180381,
        "end_time": 182990,
        "text": "ATP being the coal of the body&#39;s furnace."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 183563,
        "end_time": 185930,
        "text": "The high cost of maintaining\nresting potentials"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 185954,
        "end_time": 188194,
        "text": "in all 86 billion neurons"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 188218,
        "end_time": 189975,
        "text": "means that little energy is left"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 189999,
        "end_time": 193458,
        "text": "to propel signals down axons\nand across synapses,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 193482,
        "end_time": 196345,
        "text": "the nerve discharges\nthat actually get things done."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 196369,
        "end_time": 199289,
        "text": "Even if only a tiny percentage of neurons"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 199313,
        "end_time": 202153,
        "text": "fired in a given region at any one time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 202177,
        "end_time": 206120,
        "text": "the energy burden of generating spikes\nover the entire brain"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 206144,
        "end_time": 207438,
        "text": "would be unsustainable."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 208097,
        "end_time": 210405,
        "text": "Here&#39;s where energy efficiency comes in."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 210429,
        "end_time": 214871,
        "text": "Letting just a small proportion of cells\nsignal at any one time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 214895,
        "end_time": 216788,
        "text": "known as sparse coding,"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 216812,
        "end_time": 218348,
        "text": "uses the least energy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 218372,
        "end_time": 220642,
        "text": "but carries the most information."
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 220666,
        "end_time": 222895,
        "text": "Because the small number of signals"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 222919,
        "end_time": 226956,
        "text": "have thousands of possible paths\nby which to distribute themselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 226980,
        "end_time": 230004,
        "text": "A drawback of sparse coding\nwithin a huge number of neurons"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 230028,
        "end_time": 231330,
        "text": "is its cost."
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 231354,
        "end_time": 234155,
        "text": "Worse, if a big proportion\nof cells never fire,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 234179,
        "end_time": 235575,
        "text": "then they are superfluous"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 235599,
        "end_time": 238810,
        "text": "and evolution should have\njettisoned them long ago."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 238834,
        "end_time": 242321,
        "text": "The solution is to find\nthe optimum proportion of cells"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 242345,
        "end_time": 244372,
        "text": "that the brain can have active at once."
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 244396,
        "end_time": 245986,
        "text": "For maximum efficiency,"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 246010,
        "end_time": 250730,
        "text": "between 1% and 16% of cells\nshould be active at any given moment."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 251263,
        "end_time": 253824,
        "text": "This is the energy limit\nwe have to live with"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 253848,
        "end_time": 255372,
        "text": "in order to be conscious at all."
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 255396,
        "end_time": 256935,
        "text": "The need to conserve resources"
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 256959,
        "end_time": 259267,
        "text": "is the reason\nmost of the brain&#39;s operations"
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 259291,
        "end_time": 261697,
        "text": "must happen outside of consciousness."
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 261721,
        "end_time": 264169,
        "text": "It&#39;s why multitasking is a fool&#39;s errand."
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 264193,
        "end_time": 266947,
        "text": "We simply lack the energy\nto do two things at once,"
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 266971,
        "end_time": 268759,
        "text": "let alone three or five."
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 268783,
        "end_time": 270891,
        "text": "When we try, we do each task less well"
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 270915,
        "end_time": 273219,
        "text": "than if we had given it\nour full attention."
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 273243,
        "end_time": 274747,
        "text": "The numbers are against us."
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 275049,
        "end_time": 277387,
        "text": "Your brain is already smart and powerful."
    },
    {
        "index": 107,
        "start_time": 277411,
        "end_time": 281030,
        "text": "So powerful that it needs\na lot of power to stay powerful."
    },
    {
        "index": 108,
        "start_time": 281054,
        "end_time": 282230,
        "text": "And so smart"
    },
    {
        "index": 109,
        "start_time": 282254,
        "end_time": 284895,
        "text": "that it has built in\nan energy-efficiency plan."
    },
    {
        "index": 110,
        "start_time": 285422,
        "end_time": 287992,
        "text": "So don&#39;t let a fraudulent myth\nmake you guilty"
    },
    {
        "index": 111,
        "start_time": 288016,
        "end_time": 289799,
        "text": "about your supposedly lazy brain."
    },
    {
        "index": 112,
        "start_time": 289823,
        "end_time": 291738,
        "text": "Guilt would be a waste of energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 113,
        "start_time": 291762,
        "end_time": 292809,
        "text": "After all this,"
    },
    {
        "index": 114,
        "start_time": 292833,
        "end_time": 295281,
        "text": "don&#39;t you realize\nit&#39;s dumb to waste mental energy?"
    },
    {
        "index": 115,
        "start_time": 295305,
        "end_time": 298080,
        "text": "You have billions of\npower-hungry neurons to maintain."
    },
    {
        "index": 116,
        "start_time": 298104,
        "end_time": 299210,
        "text": "So hop to it!"
    }
]